<section id="formats">
  <div class="section-label">What we play</div>
  <div class="play-grid">

    <div class="play-card reveal reveal-delay-1">
      <div class="play-card-tag">Format</div>
      <div class="play-card-title">Americano</div>
      <div class="play-card-body">Rotating partners, everyone plays with everyone. Points-based, competitive, and a great way to get to know the whole group's game.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="play-card reveal reveal-delay-2">
      <div class="play-card-tag">Format</div>
      <div class="play-card-title">Mexicano</div>
      <div class="play-card-body">You're paired with and against players at your level as scores update in real time. Every match is competitive regardless of who's playing.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="play-card reveal reveal-delay-3">
      <div class="play-card-tag">Format</div>
      <div class="play-card-title">Spontaneous Tournaments</div>
      <div class="play-card-body">Fixed teams, bracket play, bragging rights. Organised on the night when numbers are right and the energy calls for it.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="play-card reveal reveal-delay-4">
      <div class="play-card-tag">Session</div>
      <div class="play-card-title">Drills &amp; Practice</div>
      <div class="play-card-body">Dedicated practice nights: serve patterns, wall play, volleys, lobs. Structured improvement, not just match play. One of the most underrated sessions.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="play-card reveal reveal-delay-5">
      <div class="play-card-tag">Format</div>
      <div class="play-card-title">Open Doubles</div>
      <div class="play-card-body">Pick your partner, challenge any pair. Classic padel the way it was meant to be played, on your terms, with people you trust on your side.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="play-card reveal reveal-delay-6">
      <div class="play-card-tag">Wildcard</div>
      <div class="play-card-title">Whatever the Night Calls For</div>
      <div class="play-card-body">Sometimes the group decides on the night. The format flexes around who shows up and what kind of session everyone's in the mood for.</div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<script>
  const revealObs = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
    entries.forEach(entry => {
      if (entry.isIntersecting) {
        entry.target.classList.add('visible');
        revealObs.unobserve(entry.target);
      }
    });
  }, { threshold: 0.12 });

  document.querySelectorAll('.reveal').forEach(el => revealObs.observe(el));
</script>
